WEBVTT

00:00:30.360 --> 00:00:35.500
The beginning of the Gospel of Jesus Christ, the Son of God.

00:00:36.040 --> 00:00:38.220
As it is written in the prophets,

00:00:38.540 --> 00:00:42.240
Behold, I send my messenger before thy face,

00:00:42.780 --> 00:00:45.600
Which shall prepare thy way before thee,

00:00:46.120 --> 00:00:49.620
The voice of one crying in the wilderness,

00:00:50.140 --> 00:00:53.460
Prepare ye the way of the Lord,

00:00:53.460 --> 00:00:56.260
Make his path straight.

00:00:57.140 --> 00:00:59.440
John did baptize in the wilderness,

00:00:59.960 --> 00:01:03.300
And preach the baptism of repentance

00:01:03.300 --> 00:01:05.600
For the remission of sins.

00:01:06.040 --> 00:01:11.140
And there went out unto him all the land of Judea,

00:01:11.300 --> 00:01:13.080
And they of Jerusalem,

00:01:13.480 --> 00:01:18.140
And were all baptized of him in the river of Jordan,

00:01:18.400 --> 00:01:20.220
Confessing their sins.

00:01:20.620 --> 00:01:24.300
And John was clothed with camel's hair,

00:01:24.640 --> 00:01:28.840
And with a girdle of a skin about his loins,

00:01:29.300 --> 00:01:32.900
And he did eat locusts and wild honey,

00:01:33.540 --> 00:01:35.020
And preached, saying,

00:01:35.500 --> 00:01:37.500
There cometh one mightier than I,

00:01:37.700 --> 00:01:40.740
After me, the latchet of whose shoes,

00:01:41.040 --> 00:01:46.180
I am not worthy to stoop down and unloose.

00:01:46.720 --> 00:01:50.060
I indeed have baptized you with water,

00:01:50.380 --> 00:01:55.060
But he shall baptize you with the Holy Ghost.

00:01:55.760 --> 00:01:57.860
And it came to pass in those days

00:01:57.860 --> 00:02:02.420
That Jesus came from Nazareth of Galilee,

00:02:02.740 --> 00:02:05.640
And was baptized of John in Jordan,

00:02:06.040 --> 00:02:09.020
And straightway coming up out of the water,

00:02:09.440 --> 00:02:11.540
He saw the heavens opened,

00:02:11.540 --> 00:02:16.040
And the Spirit, like a dove, descending upon him.

00:02:16.300 --> 00:02:18.800
And there came a voice from heaven, saying,

00:02:19.160 --> 00:02:25.020
Thou art my beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased.

00:02:25.840 --> 00:02:30.660
And immediately the Spirit driveth him into the wilderness.

00:02:31.620 --> 00:02:33.900
And he was there in the wilderness,

00:02:34.120 --> 00:02:37.580
Forty days, tempted of Satan,

00:02:38.080 --> 00:02:40.520
And was with the wild beast,

00:02:41.040 --> 00:02:43.520
And the angels ministered unto him.

00:02:44.320 --> 00:02:48.240
Now, after that John was put in prison,

00:02:48.840 --> 00:02:51.540
Jesus came into Galilee,

00:02:51.820 --> 00:02:55.980
Preaching the gospel of the kingdom of God,

00:02:56.360 --> 00:02:57.160
And saying,

00:02:57.640 --> 00:02:59.640
The time is fulfilled,

00:03:00.080 --> 00:03:02.780
And the kingdom of God is at hand.

00:03:03.180 --> 00:03:06.120
Repent ye, and believe the gospel.

00:03:06.120 --> 00:03:10.100
Now, as he walked by the sea of Galilee,

00:03:10.640 --> 00:03:14.160
He saw Simon and Andrew, his brother,

00:03:14.640 --> 00:03:18.120
Casting a net into the sea, for they were fishers.

00:03:18.220 --> 00:03:20.420
And Jesus said unto them,

00:03:20.600 --> 00:03:22.460
Come ye after me,

00:03:22.660 --> 00:03:26.240
And I will make you to become fishers of men.

00:03:26.700 --> 00:03:30.000
And straightway they forsook their nets and followed him.

00:03:30.460 --> 00:03:33.580
And when he had gone a little farther,

00:03:33.580 --> 00:03:37.740
Thence he saw James, the son of Zebedee,

00:03:37.900 --> 00:03:41.840
And John, his brother, who also were in the ship,

00:03:42.100 --> 00:03:43.260
Mending their nets.

00:03:43.820 --> 00:03:45.540
And straightway he called them,

00:03:45.640 --> 00:03:48.720
And they left their father Zebedee in the ship

00:03:48.720 --> 00:03:52.440
With the hired servants and went after him.

00:03:52.700 --> 00:03:55.380
And they went into Capernaum.

00:03:55.620 --> 00:03:58.120
And straightway on the Sabbath day,

00:03:58.500 --> 00:04:01.540
He entered into the synagogue and taught.

00:04:01.910 --> 00:04:04.400
And they were astonished at his doctrine,

00:04:04.860 --> 00:04:08.600
For he taught them as one that had authority,

00:04:08.940 --> 00:04:11.760
And not as the scribes.

00:04:11.920 --> 00:04:14.800
And there was in their synagogue a man

00:04:14.800 --> 00:04:17.000
With an unclean spirit.

00:04:17.360 --> 00:04:19.040
And he cried out, saying,

00:04:19.340 --> 00:04:22.680
Let us alone, what if we to do with thee,

00:04:22.780 --> 00:04:27.040
Thou Jesus of Nazareth, art thou come to destroy us?

00:04:27.040 --> 00:04:31.520
I know thee, who thou art, the holy one of God.

00:04:32.200 --> 00:04:34.560
And Jesus rebuked him, saying,

00:04:34.960 --> 00:04:37.860
Hold thy peace, and come out of him.

00:04:38.300 --> 00:04:40.840
And they were all amazed,

00:04:41.480 --> 00:04:45.640
In so much that they questioned among themselves, saying,

00:04:46.120 --> 00:04:50.000
What thing is this, what new doctrine is this?

00:04:50.300 --> 00:04:52.840
For with authority commandeth he,

00:04:52.840 --> 00:04:57.460
Even the unclean spirits, and they do obey him.

00:04:58.060 --> 00:05:00.500
And immediately his fame spread abroad,

00:05:00.840 --> 00:05:04.340
Throughout all the region round about Galilee.

00:05:04.880 --> 00:05:09.160
And forthwith, when they were come out of the synagogue,

00:05:09.580 --> 00:05:13.220
They entered into the house of Simon and Andrew,

00:05:13.620 --> 00:05:15.600
With James and John.

00:05:16.080 --> 00:05:21.260
But Simon's wife's mother lay sick of a fever and anon.

00:05:21.260 --> 00:05:26.400
They tell him of her, and he came and took her by the hand,

00:05:26.840 --> 00:05:30.260
And lifted her up, and immediately the fever left her,

00:05:30.680 --> 00:05:32.960
And she ministered unto them.

00:05:33.220 --> 00:05:36.120
And even when the sun did set,

00:05:36.380 --> 00:05:39.640
They brought unto him all that were diseased,

00:05:39.860 --> 00:05:42.540
And them that were possessed with devils,

00:05:42.740 --> 00:05:46.760
And all the city was gathered together at the door.

00:05:47.380 --> 00:05:51.420
And he healed many that were sick of divers' diseases,

00:05:52.060 --> 00:05:54.720
And cast out many devils, and suffered,

00:05:55.360 --> 00:05:58.260
Not the devils to speak because they knew him.

00:05:58.820 --> 00:06:03.520
And in the morning, rising up a great while before day,

00:06:03.660 --> 00:06:08.140
He went out and departed into a solitary place,

00:06:08.760 --> 00:06:13.980
And there prayed, And Simon and they that were with him

00:06:14.720 --> 00:06:17.560
Followed, and when they had found him,

00:06:17.660 --> 00:06:21.680
They said unto him, All men seek for thee.

00:06:22.060 --> 00:06:26.140
And he said unto them, Let us go into the next towns

00:06:26.140 --> 00:06:31.120
That I may preach there also, for therefore came I forth.

00:06:31.940 --> 00:06:36.000
And he preached in their synagogues throughout all Galilee,

00:06:36.400 --> 00:06:41.200
And cast out devils, and there came a leper to him,

00:06:41.200 --> 00:06:43.940
Beseeching him, and kneeling down to him,

00:06:44.140 --> 00:06:46.940
And saying unto him, If thou wilt,

00:06:47.480 --> 00:06:50.140
Thou canst make me clean.

00:06:50.780 --> 00:06:55.640
And Jesus, moved with compassion, put forth his hand,

00:06:55.980 --> 00:06:58.880
And touched him, and sayeth unto him,

00:06:59.320 --> 00:07:02.240
I will be thou clean.

00:07:02.880 --> 00:07:05.180
And as soon as he had spoken,

00:07:05.580 --> 00:07:09.040
Immediately the leprosy departed from him,

00:07:09.560 --> 00:07:14.120
And he was cleansed, and he straightly charged him,

00:07:14.480 --> 00:07:18.560
And forthwith sent him away, and sayeth unto him,

00:07:18.960 --> 00:07:23.040
See thou say nothing to any man, but go thy way,

00:07:23.680 --> 00:07:27.460
Show thyself to the priest, and offer for thy cleansing

00:07:27.460 --> 00:07:30.420
Those things which Moses commanded

00:07:30.880 --> 00:07:33.480
For a testimony unto them.

00:07:34.320 --> 00:07:39.020
But he went out and began to publish it much,

00:07:39.400 --> 00:07:41.660
And to blaze abroad the matter,

00:07:42.020 --> 00:07:44.920
In so much that Jesus could no more

00:07:44.920 --> 00:07:47.520
Openly enter into the city,

00:07:47.740 --> 00:07:51.180
But was without in desert places,

00:07:51.660 --> 00:07:55.320
And they came to him from every quarter.

00:07:58.920 --> 00:08:01.700
And again he entered into Capernaum,

00:08:01.700 --> 00:08:04.920
After some days, and it was noised

00:08:04.920 --> 00:08:08.800
That he was in the house, and straightway

00:08:08.800 --> 00:08:11.640
Many were gathered together, in so much that

00:08:11.640 --> 00:08:14.940
There was no room to receive them, no,

00:08:15.360 --> 00:08:17.520
Not so much as about the door,

00:08:17.740 --> 00:08:20.480
And he preached the word unto them,

00:08:20.660 --> 00:08:25.900
And they come unto him, bringing one sick of the palsy,

00:08:26.080 --> 00:08:29.760
Which was born of four, and when they could not

00:08:29.760 --> 00:08:32.560
Come nigh unto him for the press,

00:08:33.000 --> 00:08:35.920
They uncovered the roof where he was,

00:08:36.120 --> 00:08:40.400
And when they had broken it up, they let down the bed

00:08:40.400 --> 00:08:43.520
Wherein the sick of palsy lay.

00:08:44.120 --> 00:08:49.360
When Jesus saw their faith, he said unto the sick

00:08:50.320 --> 00:08:55.960
Of the palsy, son, thy sins be forgiven thee.

00:08:56.720 --> 00:09:00.520
But there was certain of the scribes sitting there

00:09:00.520 --> 00:09:02.780
And reasoning in their hearts,

00:09:03.280 --> 00:09:06.560
Why doth this man speak blasphemies?

00:09:07.180 --> 00:09:10.780
Who can forgive sins but God only?

00:09:11.440 --> 00:09:15.380
And immediately when Jesus perceived in his spirit

00:09:15.380 --> 00:09:18.200
That they so reasoned within themselves,

00:09:18.260 --> 00:09:21.580
He said unto them, why reason ye these things

00:09:21.580 --> 00:09:22.560
In your hearts?

00:09:23.120 --> 00:09:27.220
Whether it is easier to say to the sick of palsy,

00:09:27.500 --> 00:09:31.560
Thy sins be forgiven thee, or to say, arise,

00:09:32.080 --> 00:09:36.880
Take up thy bed and walk, but that ye may know

00:09:36.880 --> 00:09:41.860
That the Son of Man hath power on earth to forgive sins,

00:09:42.420 --> 00:09:47.260
He sayeth to the sick of the palsy, I say unto thee arise,

00:09:47.260 --> 00:09:52.660
And take up thy bed, and go thy way into thine house.

00:09:53.080 --> 00:09:56.880
And immediately he arose, took up the bed,

00:09:57.280 --> 00:10:00.180
And went forth before them all,

00:10:00.600 --> 00:10:06.140
In so much that they were all amazed and glorified God,

00:10:06.520 --> 00:10:09.780
Saying, we never saw it on this fashion.

00:10:10.060 --> 00:10:13.900
And he went forth again by the seaside,

00:10:13.900 --> 00:10:17.620
And all the multitude resorted unto him,

00:10:17.780 --> 00:10:19.080
And he taught them.

00:10:19.600 --> 00:10:24.900
And as he passed by, he saw Levi, the son of Alphaeus,

00:10:25.220 --> 00:10:27.280
Sitting at the receipt of custom,

00:10:27.600 --> 00:10:29.800
And said unto him, follow me.

00:10:30.540 --> 00:10:33.160
And he arose and followed him.

00:10:33.780 --> 00:10:37.660
And it came to pass that as Jesus said at meet

00:10:37.660 --> 00:10:40.940
In his house with publicans and sinners,

00:10:40.940 --> 00:10:45.700
Set also together with Jesus and his disciples.

00:10:46.120 --> 00:10:49.260
For there were many, and they followed him.

00:10:49.840 --> 00:10:52.760
And when the scribes and Pharisees saw him eat

00:10:52.760 --> 00:10:57.120
with publicans and sinners, they said unto his disciples,

00:10:57.440 --> 00:11:00.600
How is it that he eateth and drinketh

00:11:00.600 --> 00:11:02.840
with publicans and sinners?

00:11:03.380 --> 00:11:06.720
When Jesus heard it, he sayeth unto them,

00:11:07.280 --> 00:11:11.360
They that are whole have no need of the physician,

00:11:12.020 --> 00:11:13.340
but they that are sick.

00:11:14.100 --> 00:11:16.700
I came not to call the righteous,

00:11:17.360 --> 00:11:19.160
but sinners to repentance.

00:11:20.180 --> 00:11:24.260
And the disciples of John and of the Pharisees

00:11:24.260 --> 00:11:29.220
used to fast, and they come and say unto him,

00:11:29.500 --> 00:11:33.440
Why do the disciples of John and of the Pharisees fast?

00:11:33.440 --> 00:11:36.420
But thy disciples fast not.

00:11:37.040 --> 00:11:38.700
And Jesus said unto them,

00:11:39.040 --> 00:11:41.800
Can the children of the bride chamber fast

00:11:41.800 --> 00:11:44.040
while the bridegroom is with them?

00:11:44.560 --> 00:11:47.660
As long as they have the bridegroom with them,

00:11:47.780 --> 00:11:49.200
they cannot fast.

00:11:49.780 --> 00:11:53.240
But the days will come when the bridegroom

00:11:53.240 --> 00:11:55.320
shall be taken away from them,

00:11:55.360 --> 00:11:59.160
and then shall they fast in those days.

00:11:59.580 --> 00:12:06.100
No man also seweth a piece of new cloth on an old garment,

00:12:06.680 --> 00:12:09.880
else the new piece that filled it up

00:12:09.880 --> 00:12:14.840
taketh away from the old, and the rent is made worse.

00:12:15.500 --> 00:12:19.620
And no man putteth new wine into old bottles,

00:12:20.200 --> 00:12:23.100
else the new wine doth burst the bottles,

00:12:23.440 --> 00:12:27.780
and the wine is spilled, and the bottles will be marred.

00:12:27.780 --> 00:12:32.600
But new wine must be put into new bottles.

00:12:33.660 --> 00:12:37.900
And it came to pass that he went through the cornfields

00:12:37.900 --> 00:12:39.500
on the Sabbath day.

00:12:39.900 --> 00:12:42.760
And his disciples began as they went

00:12:42.760 --> 00:12:45.760
to pluck the ears of corn.

00:12:46.480 --> 00:12:49.000
And the Pharisees said unto him,

00:12:49.160 --> 00:12:53.980
Behold, why do they on the Sabbath day

00:12:53.980 --> 00:12:56.300
that which is not lawful?

00:12:56.780 --> 00:12:58.580
And he said unto them,

00:12:59.040 --> 00:13:01.480
Have ye never read what David did

00:13:01.480 --> 00:13:05.440
when he had need and wasn't hungered?

00:13:05.540 --> 00:13:08.420
He and they that were with him,

00:13:08.740 --> 00:13:11.240
how he went into the house of God

00:13:11.240 --> 00:13:14.300
in the days of Abathar, the high priest,

00:13:14.760 --> 00:13:16.640
and did eat the shewbread,

00:13:17.020 --> 00:13:21.400
which is not lawful to eat, but for the priest,

00:13:21.800 --> 00:13:24.820
and gave also to them which were with him?

00:13:25.000 --> 00:13:27.180
And he said unto them,

00:13:27.480 --> 00:13:33.100
The Sabbath was made for man and not man for the Sabbath.

00:13:33.960 --> 00:13:41.300
Therefore, the Son of Man is Lord also of the Sabbath.

00:13:48.840 --> 00:13:52.740
Reading by Simon Wainwright.

00:13:55.580 --> 00:13:56.080
Thank you.

00:14:27.074 --> 00:14:34.074
And he entered again into the synagogue, and there was a man there with a withered hand.

00:14:34.494 --> 00:14:43.474
And they watched him, whether he would heal him on the Sabbath day, that they might accuse him.

00:14:43.474 --> 00:14:49.534
And he said unto the man which had the withered hand, Stand forth.

00:14:49.994 --> 00:14:56.174
And he sayeth unto them, Is it lawful to do good on the Sabbath days,

00:14:56.614 --> 00:15:03.834
Or to do evil, to save life, or to kill? But they held their peace.

00:15:04.474 --> 00:15:11.434
And when he had looked round about on them, With anger being grieved

00:15:11.434 --> 00:15:18.114
For the hardness of their hearts, he sayeth unto the man, Stretch forth thine hand.

00:15:18.674 --> 00:15:24.294
And he stretched it out, and his hand was restored whole as the other.

00:15:24.734 --> 00:15:31.474
And the Pharisees went forth and straightway took counsel with the Herodians against him,

00:15:31.614 --> 00:15:37.694
How they might destroy him. But Jesus withdrew himself with his disciples

00:15:37.694 --> 00:15:44.414
to the sea, and a great multitude from Galilee followed him, and from Judea,

00:15:45.194 --> 00:15:50.854
and from Jerusalem, and from Edomia, and from beyond Jordan.

00:15:51.354 --> 00:15:56.274
And they about Tyree and Sidon, a great multitude,

00:15:56.774 --> 00:16:02.094
when they had heard what great things he did, came unto him.

00:16:02.094 --> 00:16:09.694
And he spake to his disciples that a small ship should wait on him because of the multitude,

00:16:10.394 --> 00:16:15.054
lest they should throng him. For he had healed many,

00:16:15.514 --> 00:16:22.654
insomuch that they pressed upon him, for to touch him as many as had plagues.

00:16:23.134 --> 00:16:27.194
And unclean spirits, when they saw him, fell down before him,

00:16:27.194 --> 00:16:35.254
and cried, saying, Thou art the Son of God. And he straightly charged them that they should not

00:16:35.254 --> 00:16:43.074
make him known. And he goeth up into a mountain, and calleth unto him whom he would.

00:16:43.274 --> 00:16:50.374
And they came unto him, and he ordained twelve, that they should be with him, and that he might

00:16:50.374 --> 00:16:58.714
send them forth to preach, and to have power to heal sicknesses, and to cast out devils.

00:16:59.154 --> 00:17:06.354
And Simon he surnamed Peter, and James the son of Zebedee, and John the brother of James,

00:17:06.474 --> 00:17:14.454
he surnamed them Boangres, which is the sons of thunder. And Andrew and Philip,

00:17:14.454 --> 00:17:21.674
and Bartholomew, and Matthew and Thomas, and James the son of Alphaeus, and Thaddeus,

00:17:21.954 --> 00:17:29.594
and Simon the Canaanite, and Judas Iscariot, which also betrayed him.

00:17:30.414 --> 00:17:37.274
And they went into in-house, and the multitude cometh together again, so that they could not

00:17:37.274 --> 00:17:44.414
much as eat bread. And when his friends heard of it, they went out to lay hold on him.

00:17:44.674 --> 00:17:52.114
And they said, He is beside himself. And the scribes which came down from Jerusalem said,

00:17:52.454 --> 00:18:00.034
He hath bells above, and by the prints of devils casteth he out devils. And he called them unto

00:18:00.034 --> 00:18:09.234
him, and saith unto them in parables, How can Satan cast out Satan? And if a kingdom be divided

00:18:09.234 --> 00:18:18.054
against itself, that kingdom cannot stand. And if a house be divided against itself, that house

00:18:18.554 --> 00:18:26.254
cannot stand. And if Satan rise up against himself, and be divided, he cannot stand,

00:18:26.254 --> 00:18:33.914
but hath an end. No man can enter into a strong man's house, and spoil his goods,

00:18:34.554 --> 00:18:42.894
except he will first bind the strong man. And then he will spoil his house. Verily I say unto you,

00:18:43.114 --> 00:18:51.474
All sins shall be forgiven unto the sons of men, and blasphemies, wherewith soever they shall

00:18:51.474 --> 00:19:01.034
blaspheme. But he that shall blaspheme against the Holy Ghost hath never forgiveness, but is in

00:19:01.034 --> 00:19:11.114
danger of eternal damnation, because they said, He hath an unclean spirit. There came then his

00:19:11.114 --> 00:19:17.354
brethren and his mother, and standing without, sent unto him, calling him. And the multitude

00:19:17.354 --> 00:19:24.914
said about him, and they said unto him, Behold thy mother and thy brethren without seek for thee.

00:19:25.514 --> 00:19:33.874
And he answered them, saying, Who is my mother or my brethren? And he looked round about on them,

00:19:34.234 --> 00:19:43.494
which said about him, and said, Behold my mother and my brethren. For whosoever shall do the will

00:19:43.494 --> 00:19:50.194
of God the same as my brother, and my sister, and my mother.

00:19:51.154 --> 00:19:59.034
And he began again to teach by the seaside, and there was gathered unto him a

00:19:59.034 --> 00:20:07.234
great multitude, so that he entered into a ship, and set in the sea. And the whole multitude was

00:20:07.234 --> 00:20:14.254
gathered by the sea on the land. And he taught them many things by parables, and said unto them

00:20:14.254 --> 00:20:23.774
in his doctrine, Hearken, behold, there went out a sower to sow. And it came to pass, as he sowed,

00:20:23.914 --> 00:20:31.814
some fell by the wayside, and the fowls of the air came, and devoured it up. And some fell on

00:20:31.814 --> 00:20:39.374
stony ground, where it had not much earth, and immediately it sprang up, because it had no depth

00:20:39.374 --> 00:20:47.354
of earth. But when the sun was up, it was scorched, and because it had no root, it withered away.

00:20:47.894 --> 00:20:55.214
And some fell among thorns, and the thorns grew up, and choked it, and it yielded no fruit.

00:20:55.844 --> 00:21:04.434
And other fell on good ground, and did yield fruit, and sprang up, and increased, and brought forth

00:21:04.434 --> 00:21:13.534
some thirty, and some sixty, and some in hundred. And he said unto them, He that hath ears to hear,

00:21:14.134 --> 00:21:22.954
let him hear. And when he was alone, they that were about him with the twelve, asked of him the

00:21:22.954 --> 00:21:30.894
parable. And he said unto them, Unto you it is given to know the mystery of the kingdom of God,

00:21:31.154 --> 00:21:39.734
but unto them that are without, all these things are done in parables. That seeing they may see,

00:21:39.974 --> 00:21:48.754
and not perceive, and hearing they may hear, and not understand, lest at any time they should be

00:21:48.754 --> 00:21:57.254
converted, and their sins should be forgiven them. And he said unto them, Know ye not this parable?

00:21:57.694 --> 00:22:07.774
And how then will ye know all parables? The sower soweth the word, and these are they by the wayside,

00:22:08.074 --> 00:22:15.674
where the word is sown. But when they have heard, Satan cometh immediately, and taketh away the word

00:22:15.674 --> 00:22:23.794
that was sown in their hearts. And these are they likewise which are sown on stony ground,

00:22:24.214 --> 00:22:30.634
who when they have heard the word, immediately receive it with gladness, and have no root in

00:22:30.634 --> 00:22:38.534
themselves, and so endure but for a time. Afterward, when affliction or persecution ariseth,

00:22:38.534 --> 00:22:46.854
for the word's sake, immediately they are offended. And these are they which are sown among thorns,

00:22:48.054 --> 00:22:54.394
such as hear the word, and the cares of this world, and the deceitfulness of riches,

00:22:54.854 --> 00:23:02.474
and the lust of other things entering in choke the word, and it becometh unfruitful.

00:23:03.174 --> 00:23:12.054
And these are they which are sown on good ground, such as hear the word, and receive it,

00:23:12.214 --> 00:23:20.334
and bring forth fruit, some thirtyfold, some sixty, and some in hundred. And he said unto them,

00:23:20.714 --> 00:23:29.274
Is a candle brought to be put under a bush, or under a bed, and not to be set on a candlestick?

00:23:30.054 --> 00:23:36.634
For there is nothing hid which shall not be manifested, neither was there anything kept

00:23:36.634 --> 00:23:45.794
secret but that it should come abroad. If any man hath ears to hear, let him hear. And he said unto

00:23:45.794 --> 00:23:53.214
them, Take heed what ye hear, with what measure ye meet it shall be measured to you, and unto you

00:23:53.214 --> 00:24:02.854
hear shall more be given. For he that hath to him shall be given, and he that hath not from him

00:24:02.854 --> 00:24:12.094
shall be taken even that which he hath. And he said, So is the kingdom of God, as if a man

00:24:12.094 --> 00:24:20.854
should cast seed into the ground, and should sleep and rise night and day, and the seed should

00:24:20.854 --> 00:24:27.214
spring and grow up. He knoweth not how. For the earth bringeth forth fruit of herself,

00:24:27.734 --> 00:24:36.974
first the blade, then the ear, after that the full corn in the ear. But when the fruit is

00:24:36.974 --> 00:24:44.134
brought forth, immediately he putteth in the sickle, because the harvest is come. And he said,

00:24:44.134 --> 00:24:52.114
Whereunto shall we liken the kingdom of God, or with what comparison shall we compare it?

00:24:52.694 --> 00:25:00.794
It is like a grain of mustard seed, which when it is sown in the earth is less than all the seeds

00:25:00.794 --> 00:25:09.174
that be in the earth. But when it is sown it groweth up, and becomeeth greater than all herbs,

00:25:09.174 --> 00:25:16.274
and shooteth out great branches, so that the fowls of the air may lodge under the shadow of it.

00:25:16.854 --> 00:25:24.134
And with many such parables spake he the word unto them, as they were able to hear it.

00:25:24.874 --> 00:25:32.654
But without a parable spake he not unto them, and when they were alone he expounded all things

00:25:32.654 --> 00:25:40.354
to his disciples. And the same day when the even was come, he sayeth unto them,

00:25:40.654 --> 00:25:48.014
Let us pass over on to the other side. And when they had sent away the multitude,

00:25:48.514 --> 00:25:56.794
they took him even as he was in the ship, and there were also with him other little ships.

00:25:56.794 --> 00:26:05.734
And there arose a great storm of wind, and the waves beat into the ship, so that it was now full.

00:26:06.074 --> 00:26:12.874
And he was in the hinder part of the ship, asleep on a pillow. And they awake him,

00:26:13.174 --> 00:26:23.054
and say unto him, Master, carest thou not that we perish? And he arose and rebuked the wind,

00:26:23.054 --> 00:26:31.694
and said unto the sea, Peace, be still. And the wind ceased, and there was a great calm.

00:26:32.374 --> 00:26:38.994
And he said unto them, Why are ye so fearful? How is it that ye have no faith?

00:26:39.554 --> 00:26:46.294
And they feared exceedingly, and said one to another, What manner of man is this,

00:26:46.294 --> 00:26:50.674
that even the wind and the sea obey him?

00:27:33.655 --> 00:27:41.255
And they came over onto the other side of the sea, into the country of the Gadarenes.

00:27:41.635 --> 00:27:47.975
And when he was come out of the ship, immediately there met him, out of the tombs,

00:27:48.335 --> 00:27:56.875
a man with an unclean spirit, who had his dwelling among the tombs, and no man could bind him.

00:27:56.875 --> 00:28:05.595
No, not with chains, because that he had been often bound with fetters and chains,

00:28:06.075 --> 00:28:13.095
and the chains had been plucked asunder by him, and the fetters broken into pieces,

00:28:13.755 --> 00:28:16.695
neither could any man tame him.

00:28:17.775 --> 00:28:28.415
And always, night and day, he was in the mountains and in the tombs, crying and cutting himself with stones.

00:28:28.855 --> 00:28:36.755
But when he saw Jesus afar off, he ran and worshipped him, and cried with a loud voice,

00:28:37.055 --> 00:28:43.855
and said, What have I to do with thee, Jesus, thou son of the Most High God?

00:28:43.855 --> 00:28:49.035
I adjure thee, by God, that thou torment me not.

00:28:50.055 --> 00:28:56.295
For he said unto him, Come out of the man, thou unclean spirit.

00:28:57.695 --> 00:29:00.755
And he asked him, What is thy name?

00:29:01.055 --> 00:29:06.335
And he answered, saying, My name is Legion, for we are many.

00:29:07.095 --> 00:29:13.375
And he besought him much, that he would not send him away out of the country.

00:29:13.375 --> 00:29:21.015
Now there was there, nigh unto the mountains, a great herd of swine feeding.

00:29:21.735 --> 00:29:28.475
And all the devils besought him, saying, Send us into the swine, that we may enter into them.

00:29:29.475 --> 00:29:32.115
And forthwith Jesus gave them leave.

00:29:32.595 --> 00:29:36.675
And the unclean spirits went out and entered into the swine,

00:29:37.035 --> 00:29:42.155
and the herd ran violently down a steep place into the sea.

00:29:42.155 --> 00:29:47.855
They were about two thousand, and were choked in the sea.

00:29:48.515 --> 00:29:55.515
And they that fed the swine fled, and told it in the city and in the country.

00:29:55.915 --> 00:30:00.515
And they went out to see what it was that was done.

00:30:01.515 --> 00:30:08.415
And they came to Jesus to see him that was possessed with the devil and the legion,

00:30:08.415 --> 00:30:12.515
sitting and clothed in his right mind.

00:30:13.035 --> 00:30:15.555
And they were afraid.

00:30:16.275 --> 00:30:25.835
And they that saw it told them how it befell to him that was possessed with the devil and also concerning the swine.

00:30:25.935 --> 00:30:29.535
And they began to pray him to depart out of their coast.

00:30:29.835 --> 00:30:37.335
And when he was come into the ship, he that had been possessed with the devil prayed him that he might be with him.

00:30:38.135 --> 00:30:42.215
Howbeit Jesus suffered him not, but saith unto him,

00:30:42.575 --> 00:30:51.675
Go home to thy friends, and tell them how great things the Lord hath done for thee, and hath had compassion on thee.

00:30:52.235 --> 00:31:00.255
And he departed and began to publish in Decapolis how great things Jesus had done for him.

00:31:00.255 --> 00:31:02.555
And all men did marvel.

00:31:03.075 --> 00:31:08.595
And when Jesus was passed over again by ship unto the other side,

00:31:09.075 --> 00:31:14.015
much people gathered unto him, and he was nigh unto the sea.

00:31:14.435 --> 00:31:20.275
And, behold, there cometh one of the rulers of the synagogue, Jarius by name.

00:31:20.635 --> 00:31:23.835
And when he saw him, he fell at his feet.

00:31:24.755 --> 00:31:30.755
And he besought him greatly, saying, My little daughter lieth at the point of death.

00:31:30.875 --> 00:31:38.715
I pray thee, come and lay thy hands on her, that she may be healed and she may live.

00:31:39.575 --> 00:31:45.015
And Jesus went with him, and much people followed him and thronged him.

00:31:45.015 --> 00:31:50.175
And a certain woman, which had an issue of blood twelve years,

00:31:50.495 --> 00:31:56.855
and had suffered many things of many physicians, and had spent all that she had,

00:31:57.175 --> 00:32:01.475
and was nothing bettered, but rather grew worse.

00:32:02.155 --> 00:32:09.195
When she had heard of Jesus, came in the press behind, and touched his garment.

00:32:09.195 --> 00:32:14.955
For she said, If I may touch but his clothes, I shall be whole.

00:32:15.355 --> 00:32:18.815
And straightway the fountain of her blood was dried up,

00:32:19.155 --> 00:32:23.695
and she felt in her body that she was healed of that plague.

00:32:24.575 --> 00:32:29.755
And Jesus, immediately knowing in himself that virtue had gone out of him,

00:32:30.215 --> 00:32:35.875
turned him about in the press, and said, Who touched my clothes?

00:32:35.875 --> 00:32:42.295
And his disciples said unto him, Thou seest the multitude thronging thee,

00:32:42.615 --> 00:32:44.755
and sayest thou who touched me?

00:32:45.295 --> 00:32:49.855
And he looked round about to see her that had done this thing.

00:32:50.315 --> 00:32:55.235
But the woman, fearing and trembling, knowing what was done in her,

00:32:55.435 --> 00:33:00.835
came and fell down before him, and told him all the truth.

00:33:00.835 --> 00:33:07.235
And he said unto her, Daughter, thy faith hath made thee whole.

00:33:07.555 --> 00:33:10.635
Go in peace, and be whole of thy plague.

00:33:11.515 --> 00:33:16.155
While he yet spake, there came, from the ruler of the synagogue's house,

00:33:16.395 --> 00:33:23.335
certain which said, Thy daughter is dead. Why troublest thou the master any further?

00:33:24.375 --> 00:33:27.315
As soon as Jesus heard the word that was spoken,

00:33:27.315 --> 00:33:33.335
he saith unto the ruler of the synagogue, Be not afraid, only believe.

00:33:34.595 --> 00:33:43.495
And he suffered no man to follow him save Peter and James and John the brother of James.

00:33:44.395 --> 00:33:48.075
And he cometh to the house of the ruler of the synagogue,

00:33:48.635 --> 00:33:53.895
and seeth the tumult and them that wept and wailed greatly.

00:33:53.895 --> 00:34:00.675
And when he was come in, he saith unto them, Why make ye this ado and weep?

00:34:00.795 --> 00:34:04.055
The damsel is not dead, but sleepeth.

00:34:04.475 --> 00:34:09.515
And they laughed him to scorn, but when he had put them all out,

00:34:10.255 --> 00:34:15.915
he taketh the father and the mother of the damsel and them that were with him,

00:34:16.155 --> 00:34:19.735
and entereth in where the damsel was lying.

00:34:19.735 --> 00:34:23.755
And he took the damsel by the hand and said unto her,

00:34:24.515 --> 00:34:31.235
Talitha cum I, which is being interpreted, Damsel, I say unto thee arise.

00:34:32.195 --> 00:34:39.055
And straightway the damsel arose and walked, for she was of the age of twelve years,

00:34:39.655 --> 00:34:43.915
and they were astonished with a great astonishment.

00:34:43.915 --> 00:34:48.415
And he charged them straightly that no man should know it,

00:34:48.595 --> 00:34:52.575
and commanded that something should be given her to eat.

00:34:55.895 --> 00:35:02.075
And he went out from thence, and came into his own country, and his disciples follow him.

00:35:02.695 --> 00:35:07.575
And when the Sabbath day was come, he began to teach in the synagogue.

00:35:07.915 --> 00:35:11.075
And many hearing him were astonished, saying,

00:35:11.075 --> 00:35:17.455
From whence hath this man these things, and what wisdom is this which is given unto him,

00:35:17.715 --> 00:35:21.855
that even such mighty works are wrought by his hands?

00:35:22.535 --> 00:35:31.075
Is not this the carpenter, the son of Mary, the brother of James, and Osais, and Judah, and Simon,

00:35:31.395 --> 00:35:36.255
and are not his sisters here with us? And they were offended at him.

00:35:36.255 --> 00:35:43.595
But Jesus said unto them, A prophet is not without honor, but in his own country,

00:35:43.855 --> 00:35:48.155
and among his own kin, and in his own house.

00:35:48.895 --> 00:35:57.395
And he could there do no mighty work, save that he laid his hands upon a few sick folk and healed them.

00:35:57.795 --> 00:36:05.035
And he marveled because of their unbelief, and he went round about the village's teaching.

00:36:05.035 --> 00:36:12.735
And he called unto him the Twelve, and began to send them forth by two and two,

00:36:13.115 --> 00:36:20.435
and gave them power over unclean spirits, and commanded them that they should take nothing for their journey,

00:36:20.995 --> 00:36:32.475
save a staff only, no script, no bread, no money in their purse, but be shod with sandals, and not put on two coats.

00:36:32.475 --> 00:36:42.615
And he said unto them, In what place soever ye enter into, in house, there abide till ye depart from that place.

00:36:43.315 --> 00:36:51.795
And whosoever shall not receive you, nor hear you, when ye depart thence, shake off the dust under your feet,

00:36:51.795 --> 00:37:04.515
for a testimony against them, verily I say unto you, it shall be more tolerable for Sodom and Gomorrah in the day of judgment than for that city.

00:37:05.135 --> 00:37:16.015
And they went out and preached that men should repent, and they cast out many devils, and anointed with oil many that were sick and healed them.

00:37:16.015 --> 00:37:25.815
And King Herod heard of him, for his name was spread abroad, and he said that John the Baptist was risen from the dead,

00:37:26.175 --> 00:37:31.235
and therefore mighty works do show forth themselves in him.

00:37:31.595 --> 00:37:38.895
Others said that it is Elias, and others said that it is a prophet, or as one of the prophets.

00:37:38.895 --> 00:37:48.315
But when Herod heard thereof, he said, It is John whom I beheaded, he is risen from the dead.

00:37:48.635 --> 00:38:00.055
For Herod himself had sent forth, and laid hold upon John, and bound him in prison for Herodias' sake, his brother Phillips' wife.

00:38:00.055 --> 00:38:10.455
For he had married her. For John had said unto Herod, It is not lawful for thee to have thy brother's wife.

00:38:10.955 --> 00:38:18.555
Therefore Herodias had a quarrel against him, and would have him killed, but she could not.

00:38:18.555 --> 00:38:27.115
For Herod feared John, knowing that he was a just man, and unholy, and observed him.

00:38:27.395 --> 00:38:32.395
And when he heard him, he did many things, and heard him gladly.

00:38:33.255 --> 00:38:44.415
And when a convenient day was come, that Herod, on his birthday, made a supper to his lords, high captains, and chief estates of Galilee.

00:38:44.415 --> 00:38:57.155
And when the daughter of the said Herodias came in, and danced, and pleased Herod, and them that sat with him, the king said unto the damsel,

00:38:57.835 --> 00:39:10.875
Ask of me whatsoever thou wilt, and I will give it thee. And he sware unto her, Whatsoever thou shall ask of me, I will give it thee unto the half of my kingdom.

00:39:10.875 --> 00:39:22.335
And she went forth, and said unto her mother, What shall I ask? And she said, The head of John the Baptist.

00:39:23.235 --> 00:39:37.835
And she came in straightway with haste unto the king, and asked, saying, I will that thou give me, by and by, in a charger, the head of John the Baptist.

00:39:37.835 --> 00:39:50.075
And the king was exceeding sorry, yet for his oaths sake, and for their sakes which set with him, he would not reject her.

00:39:50.375 --> 00:39:55.575
And immediately the king sent an executioner, and commanded his head to be brought.

00:39:55.575 --> 00:40:07.115
And he went and beheaded him in the prison, and brought his head in a charger, and gave it to the damsel, and the damsel gave it to her mother.

00:40:08.015 --> 00:40:16.715
And when his disciples heard of it, they came and took up his corpse, and laid it in a tomb.

00:40:16.715 --> 00:40:26.935
And the apostles gathered themselves together unto Jesus, and told him all things, both what they had done, and what they had taught.

00:40:27.655 --> 00:40:43.655
And he said unto them, Come ye yourselves apart into a desert place, and rest awhile, for there are many coming and going, and they had no leisure so much as to eat.

00:40:43.655 --> 00:41:00.895
And they departed into a desert place by ship, privately. And the people saw them departing, and many knew him, and ran afoot thither out of all cities, and out went them, and came together unto him.

00:41:00.895 --> 00:41:12.995
And Jesus, when he came out, saw much people, and was moved with compassion toward them, because they were as sheep, not having a shepherd.

00:41:13.635 --> 00:41:26.575
And he began to teach them many things. And when the day was now far spent, his disciples came unto him, and said, This is a desert place, and now the time is far past.

00:41:26.575 --> 00:41:37.555
Send them away, that they may go into the country round about, and into the villages, and buy themselves bread, for they have nothing to eat.

00:41:37.555 --> 00:41:51.215
He answered and said unto them, Give ye them to eat. And they say unto him, Shall we go and buy two hundred penny worth of food, and give them to eat?

00:41:51.215 --> 00:42:09.395
And he sayeth unto them, How many loaves have ye? Go and see. And when they knew, they say, Five and two fishes. And he commanded them to make all sit down by companies upon the green grass.

00:42:09.395 --> 00:42:27.195
And they sat down in ranks by hundreds and by fifties. And when he had taken the five loaves and the two fish, he looked up to heaven and blessed, and break the loaves, and gave them to his disciples to set before them.

00:42:27.195 --> 00:42:41.795
And the two fishes divided he among them all. And they did all eat and were filled. And they took up twelve baskets full of the fragments and of the fish.

00:42:41.795 --> 00:43:01.295
And they that did eat of the loaves were about five thousand men. And straightway he constrained his disciples to get into the ship and to go to the other side before unto Bethesda, while he sent away the people.

00:43:01.295 --> 00:43:15.775
And when he had sent them away, he departed into a mountain to pray. And when even was come, the ship was in the midst of the sea, and he alone on the land.

00:43:15.775 --> 00:43:30.575
And he saw them toiling and rowing, for the wind was contrary unto them. And about the fourth watch of the night he cometh unto them, walking upon the sea, and would have passed by them.

00:43:30.575 --> 00:43:47.835
But when they saw him walking upon the sea, they supposed it had been a spirit, and cried out. For they all saw him, and were troubled. And immediately he talked with them, and sayeth unto them, Be of good cheer, it is I, be not afraid.

00:43:47.835 --> 00:43:58.355
And when he went up unto them into the ship, and the wind ceased, they were sore amazed in themselves, beyond measure, and wondered.

00:43:58.355 --> 00:44:14.155
For they considered not the miracle of the loaves, for their heart was hardened. And when they had passed over, they came into the land of Geneseret, and drew to the shore.

00:44:14.155 --> 00:44:31.215
And when they were come out of the ship straightway, they knew him, and ran through that whole region round about, and began to carry about in bids those that were sick, where they heard he was.

00:44:31.215 --> 00:44:48.595
And whither soe'er he entered into villages, or cities, or country, they laid the sick in the streets, and besought him, that they might touch, if it were. But the border of his garment, and as many as touched him, were made whole.

00:45:03.015 --> 00:45:03.075
Thank you.

